`types-aiobotocore[timestream-query]` with services you use in your environment: ```bash python -m pip install 'types-aiobotocore[timestream-query]' ``` - install cancelqueryrequestrequesttypedef def get_value() -> cancelqueryrequestrequesttypedef: return {...} ``` ## how it works fully automated [mypy-boto3-builder](https://github.com/youtype/mypy_boto3_builder) carefully generates type annotations for each service, patiently waiting for `aiobotocore` updates. it delivers drop-in type annotations for you and makes sure that: - all available `aiobotocore` services are covered. - each public class and method of every `aiobotocore` service gets valid type annotations extracted from `botocore` schemas. - type annotations include up-to-date documentation. - link to documentation is provided for every method. - code is processed by [black](https://github.com/psf/black) and [isort](https://github.com/pycqa/isort) for readability. ## what's new ### implemented features - fully type annotated `boto3`, `botocore`, `aiobotocore` and `aioboto3` libraries - `mypy`, `pyright`, - generated `literals` for each service - auto discovery of types for `boto3.client` and `boto3.resource` calls - auto discovery of types for `session.client` and `session.resource` calls - auto discovery of types for `client.get_waiter` and `client.get_paginator` calls - auto discovery of types for `serviceresource` and `resource` collections - auto discovery of types for `aiobotocore.session.create_client` calls ### latest changes builder changelog can be found in [releases](https://github.com/youtype/mypy_boto3_builder/releases). ## versioning documentation_summary: The HTML text describes the PyPI (Python Package Index) listing for "types-aiobotocore-timestream-query" version 2.12.1, released on March 5, 2024. This package provides type annotations for the aiobotocore.TimestreamQuery service, generated with mypy-boto3-builder 7.23.2, and is intended to help developers by enabling better autocomplete and error detection in IDEs like VSCode, PyCharm, Emacs, and Sublime Text. It requires Python version 3.8 or higher and is licensed under the MIT License. The package supports various features including client and paginator annotations, literals, and type definitions for enhanced type checking and code completion. Installation instructions for different environments and IDEs are provided, along with information on how to uninstall the package.
